body:
### Summary
This patch fixes two issues that cause `wait(variable)` inside an interface
`initial` block to hang when the variable is written through a virtual interface
function call and the interface also contains an `always @*` block that
references `process::self()` (e.g. via UVM macros like `` `uvm_fatal ``).

Discovered while running the UVM testbench on cv32e40p (core-v-verif) https://github.com/openhwgroup/core-v-verif/pull/2724 . 
Also Related to Issue #5116; 
Independent of but complementary to #7323.

### Reproducer
```systemverilog
interface my_if();
  logic clk;
  realtime clk_period;
  bit clk_active = 0;

  initial begin
    wait (clk_active);
    forever begin
      #(clk_period);
      if (clk_active) begin
        case (clk)
          1'b0: clk = 1'b1;
          default: clk = 1'b0;
        endcase
      end
    end
  end

  always @* begin
    if (clk_active && clk_period == 0.0) begin
      automatic process p = process::self();
      $stop;
    end
  end

  function void set_period(realtime p);
    clk_period = p;
  endfunction

  function void start_clk();
    if (clk_period) clk_active = 1;
  endfunction
endinterface

class Driver;
  virtual my_if vif;
  task run();
    vif.set_period(5ns);
    #10;
    vif.start_clk();
  endtask
endclass

module t;
  my_if intf_a();
  my_if intf_b();
  initial begin
    automatic Driver d = new;
    d.vif = intf_a;
    d.run();
    repeat (4) @(posedge intf_a.clk);
    $write("*-* All Finished *-*\n");
    $finish;
  end
  initial begin #1000; $finish; end
endmodule
```

On master: simulation hangs with zero output (exit code 124 on timeout).

### Changes

- `V3Timing.cpp` (TimingControlVisitor::visit(AstAlways*)): Do not mark
combinational always blocks (hasCombo() sensitivity) as T_SUSPENDEE
when they only need process context (T_HAS_PROC). Combo blocks have no
timing controls and would spin forever as coroutines with no co_await.
This is the primary fix that resolves the hang.
- `V3Width.cpp` (methodCallIfaceRef): When a function or task is called
through a virtual interface, mark all member variables of the interface
as sensIfacep. Without this, optimization passes (V3Gate) may
constant-fold wait(variable) to wait(0) when the variable is only
written through VIF function calls (not direct member access), because
sensIfacep was only set for the vif.member path, not the
vif.function() path. This second issue is only observable with multiple
interface instances (where VIF write resolution picks one instance, leaving
others appear undriven — see #5116). A standalone test for this is deferred
until #5116 is resolved.


### Test
Added test_regress/t/t_wait_iface_vif.{v,py} — exercises the always @* + process::self() + wait() + VIF function call pattern. Confirms the primary fix (V3Timing combo block). The V3Width change is exercised (code path covered) but not independently asserted due to #5116. 

Note: locally tested with #7323 applied on top -- the multi-instance VIF
test (which exercises the V3Width `sensIfacep` fix) passes. Happy to wait for #7323 to land before merging this, or rebase as needed.

